full_text:
Sweep is making the radio tune across the band, the modes are random, linear or manual. Random jumps arounds around the band-randomly, the idea being that the entities would comtrol the sweep by affecting the white noise transistor, and they did say they do that. Linear is a smooth sweep up, then back down the band, the entities seem to have an easier time tracking the linear sweep. Manual is done by hand on a cheapy radio with a tuning knob, it&#39;s easier wiht a radio that has a tuning knob that does the half turn from one end of the band to the other. 

 When I first started using linear mode, I couldn&#39;t hear any of the usual voices, then all the sudden, I could hear it. So I&#39;m uncertain if it&#39;s the brain that has to adjust, of what if you have to create/allow the possiblity? I used to use radnom exclusivley, and that worked well, now I get litte with random mode. 

 I use linear now becuase it&#39;s much easier to get the circuit to work. Random can be finicky, as you&#39;re trying to get random pulses to be amplified, and passed through the circuit.

 Frank-S

